steps.description:
Fold the leaf in half, backwards with the crease running along the top of the rolled/folded leaf. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cb/Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cb/Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Roll the sides inward, following the same way you folded/rolled the previous leaf but this time, bend the edges/ends outward so they resemble a flowering petal. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Glue the ends and hold until dry. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Roses-from-Leaves-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
